text: Tawakalt Yekeen (born 1 August 2001) is a Nigerian track cyclist. She won multiple medals at the African championships. In 2020, she won the bronze medal in the Keirin at the African Championships in Cairo. The following year, at the African Championships, which also took place in Cairo, she won three medals: gold in the team sprint and in the team pursuit and silver in the Madison. She competed at the 2021 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. == References == Category:2001 births Category:Cyclists Category:Living people Category:People from Oyo State
